
[1]devilish

   DEVILISH, a.

   1. Partaking of the qualities of the devil; diabolical; very evil and
   mischievous; malicious; as a devilish scheme; devilish wickedness.

   2. Having communication with the devil; pertaining to the devil.

   3. Excessive; enormous; in a vulgar and ludicrous sense; as a devilish
   cheat.
